node.statement: Step 1.3.3 (q-deformed BPS partition function): In the large SU(2) charge regime (J3 ~ j^2/2), the q-BPS partition function is Z^BPS_q(j) = sum_s d_s(j,q) q_BPS^s = 2 prod_{m=1}^{j} (1 + q_BPS^m + q_BPS^{2m}), where the product structure reflects the factorization of the Hilbert space into z-modes and +-modes. For q=1 this reproduces Z^BPS from BLM. The total count D^BPS_q = Z^BPS_q(1) = 2 times 3^j is q-independent (it counts states topologically).
